Dialogue: 5,0:00:01.80,0:00:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The salinity for the Narunami region at noon should be approximately 57 ppm,
Dialogue: 5,0:00:05.98,0:00:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is expected to rise to approximately 60 ppm by six o'clock this evening.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:10.03,0:00:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to the saltflake snow,
Dialogue: 5,0:00:11.90,0:00:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the {water }temperature is expected to drop,
Dialogue: 5,0:00:13.90,0:00:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,with the temperature of Shioshishio going down to 15 degrees Celsius.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:17.37,0:00:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Next up is the weather on the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:19.28,0:00:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It actually falls on the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:20.12,0:00:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}The Shioshishio Peninsula will continue to be sunny.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:22.27,0:00:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The saltflake snow?
Dialogue: 5,0:00:23.58,0:00:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what that was.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:26.34,0:00:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It was different... maybe even a little creepy.{The punctuation here should technically be a dash. It's an alternate predicate for the preceding sentence. I could've punctuated it with a period, too, since these are subs after all. But he trails off in the audio quite a bit, so I think it's all right.}
Dialogue: 5,0:00:30.59,0:00:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if everyone in Shishio knows about how it fell on the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:34.32,0:00:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as they find out,
Dialogue: 5,0:00:36.20,0:00:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll pin the blame on Ooshi{'s} refusing to do the Boatdrift Ceremony,
Dialogue: 5,0:00:39.50,0:00:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll say the sea god's just meting out divine punishment.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:44.27,0:00:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You really think so?
Dialogue: 5,0:00:45.58,0:00:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing Dad and the others, \Nit's bound to happen that way.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:49.97,0:00:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 5,0:00:51.57,0:00:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Dad's worried about you.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:55.28,0:00:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's{ ridiculous}—
Dialogue: 5,0:00:56.03,0:00:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hikari, I think you should go home after all.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:59.03,0:01:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying—
Dialogue: 5,0:01:01.95,0:01:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:02.82,0:01:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I grabbed a bunch{handful} of snow and made this.{a saltball?}
Dialogue: 5,0:01:07.19,0:01:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The heck is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:08.81,0:01:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A fish cake?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:09.98,0:01:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a {snow }sea slug!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:12.43,0:01:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You could tell{ what it was}, right, Aka{-chan}?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:15.37,0:01:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet!{I'm not stupid like my brother.}{I love this comment.}
Dialogue: 5,0:01:18.19,0:01:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:19.08,0:01:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A sea slug should have these.{Apparently, they're (optical) tentacles, not antennae.}
Dialogue: 5,0:01:23.51,0:01:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it last until Daddy gets home?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:26.52,0:01:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it won't melt that fast.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:28.14,0:01:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? I'm so glad!{That's great.}
Dialogue: 5,0:01:30.97,0:01:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Daddy will know what it is...
Dialogue: 5,0:01:32.70,0:01:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course he will!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:33.80,0:01:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at how cute it is!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:40.03,0:01:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that saltflake snow fell on the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:43.08,0:01:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's gonna keep getting colder, like the prophecy says?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:47.96,0:01:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're not the ones \Nneglecting the sea god!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:51.94,0:01:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, haven't you noticed how our \Nspirit fire's been going out faster lately?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:56.90,0:01:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 5,0:02:02.67,0:02:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Head Priest!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:04.00,0:02:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what's going on?
Dialogue: 5,0:02:05.68,0:02:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 5,0:02:07.68,0:02:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Head Priest!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:08.68,0:02:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all so noisy.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:10.79,0:02:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{replace}L-Lord Uroko{U-Uroko-sama}.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:13.01,0:02:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Come{,} now. Hurry up{,} and sit down.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:19.31,0:02:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{replace}Lord Uroko{Uroko-sama}, if you would.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:21.60,0:02:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There is but one reason I have asked you all to gather here today:
Dialogue: 5,0:02:25.89,0:02:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I must talk to you about the calamity approaching us.
